    <header>
      <h2>The task</h2>
    </header>
    <p>
      Brian provides the markup, below, and you style it to be a basic iPhone 4 layout. To make it reasonable, he wants the flat layout of iOS 7. And you can ignore things like the status bar at the top, and all of the images. This is just a dumb prototype-like proof of concept. Make up the spacing values, he doesn't care.
    </p>
    <p>
      All he wants is square apps that flow from left to right, wrapping into the next row, all spaced evenly. The space on the sides and top of the screen must match the space between the apps. Save the "app name" area for last. Almost no one gets that far anyway. Try to set up the dock as well.
    </p>
    <img class="block-center block p" src="/images/thoughts/interview-question/ios7-on-iphone4.jpg" alt="Screen capture of iPhone 4 with iOS 7 installed" />
    <p>
      Brian says up front, "You don't need to look up anything. I can answer any question you will need to solve this. I am your Google. Ask me anything."
    </p>
    <p>
      "Oh, and I want it to be fully responsive. Everything should resize proportionally based on the width of the screen."
    </p>
    <p>
      "...and no VWs."
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

